  "body": "Right now, `helm version` output looks like this:\r\n\r\n```console\r\nENG000656:service-catalog aaronschlesinger$ helm version\r\nClient: &version.Version{SemVer:\"v2.0.1\", GitCommit:\"dc87ea8dd0111164c720fd13b4eb8a905f97ac62\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\r\nServer: &version.Version{SemVer:\"v2.0.1\", GitCommit:\"dc87ea8dd0111164c720fd13b4eb8a905f97ac62\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is fairly hard to parse in code, so it would be nice to have a `helm` command that produced more easily parsable version output. Shell scripts and similar code that reads STDOUT data would be the primary consumers of this output.\r\n\r\nSee below for an example (solely for illustrative purposes, not intended to indicate what I think a final design should look like):\r\n\r\n```console\r\nENG000656:service-catalog aaronschlesinger$ helm version --short\r\nclient=v2.0.1\r\nserver=v2.0.1\r\n```",
